' Consumer for the PKG-02b security fixture: it imports the malicious
' `sec_confused_computed` package whose compiled IR does a member access on a
' *computed* Integer (a `Binary` result). Before the IR carried result types
' the semantic checker skipped such a target; the typed IR (plan-20-B) lets
' plan-20-C's verifier resolve the computed type and reject the confusion, so
' the build must fail during IR semantic verification rather than lowering it.
IMPORT io
IMPORT sec_confused_computed AS sec_confused_computed

FUNC main AS Integer
  io::print(toString(sec_confused_computed::run()))
  RETURN 0
END FUNC
